      <label class="modal-close" for="modal-6"></label>
      <h1>Project Length</h1>
      <p class="modal-intro">The length of your project is an important factor to consider when raising money for a cause; people are unlikely to pledge to a cause that is too long or too short.</p>
      <p class="modal-content">The longest a project can run for is 182 days (6 months). However, remember when setting your target that a longer duration is not necessarily better. The same goes for if a project is too short. The shortest a project can for is 7 days (one week). The length of time your project runs for, will be dependent on how much money you need to raise. Think carefully about how much you need to raise and try to match this with the length of time your project runs for.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

